[SN]TITLE[SN]
Aberdeen FC talks to be held over Pittodrie catering

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Officials at Aberdeen FC are to hold talks with caterers at Pittodrie after complaints from fans.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The club said in a statement it had been made aware of "various issues" experienced by supporters.
Complaints are understood to have been made about the quality of catering offered and products running out.
The statement said: "We take matters such as these which directly impact upon the match-day experience for our valued fans very seriously."
The statement explained: "As a club we have made considerable investment to improve and upgrade the kiosk facilities which are currently run by our catering partners Sodexo Prestige so it is disappointing to learn that issues continue to arise.
"We wish to assure all our supporters we will be working directly with Sodexo Prestige management team in an effort to make the necessary improvements required in the interest of our supporters."
Social media responses to the news included: "Nice to see AFC have taken note of comments made regarding this. Hopefully Sodexo will take it seriously."
However another fan said: "Been going to games for 19 years, never had a problem. Be interested to know what the apparent issue is."
